549255312058735926_2009214.caption:
Strawberry Green
--------------------------------
Here's another recipe for "juice." The reason I put juice in quotes is that I'm using a different machine to produce this particular dink. Traditionally I use a juicer to make my juices but I recently got a Nutribullet.
So the process to make a drink is a bit different.  The biggest different is that you have to have liquid as part of the mix.  And the other thing so far that I have found is that there is a lot more pulp when creating my other juices.
But with that said: here's Strawberry Green:
Handful of greens.
-kale, spinach, chard
5 strawberries
1 small orange
1 - 8oz can of 100% pineapple juice.

Now blend.

--------------------------------
I started juicing as part of my healthy eating habits.  Inspired after watching; Fat, Sick, and Nearly Dying a film by Joe Cross.  I recommend everyone watch it if you haven't already.  I decided that I could incorporate juicing as part of my normal diet.  The one thing so far that I like about juicing is that I get more vegetables and fruits.  And so far I'm starting to feel that I have more energy and feel a lot better.
--------------------------------
Here's the recipe for "Green Envy"
1 Bushel of Kale
1 stalk of Celery
1/2 bulb of Fennel
2 cucumbers
3 green apples

859155946949292793_32026259.caption:
365. What does this number mean today? Today it is not just the number of days a year has or a random chosen number made from 3 units.

Today this number is meaningful. 365 days ago I had the first date and kiss with one of the most special person in my life.

Carlotta, you have become essential in my daily life, and even though sometimes the distance is not uncommon between us, I can always feel you next to me. For the good and for the bad. 
I am aware that I have my character and I know my weaknesses, but I have to say that together we jumped, I think I can say, very big and difficult barriers.

If we look at the whole year we experienced a lot more than any of us could imagine that Friday 22nd in Beijing . We saw each other in very different scenarios. Berlin, Beijing, Catalunya, Formentera, Thailand, Cambodia, Vietnam and Belgium. With friends, with family or alone. All these combined made our first chapter.

And you know what I like most about 1st chapters? That is just the beginning, the introduction, of a story.

Now it is time to summarize, to look back and remember the start of everything and how it changed. If I'd have to do it with our year I would assure you that this first part gives me confidence and energy to open all the rest of parts we have in front of us.

From Barcelona's airport going to Bologna, to Hangzhou (China). And remember kilometers are not making our relation more difficult, they are just making our relation stronger.

P.S. T'ESTIMO.

907376769907596679_328694646.caption:
Today marks ONE YEAR since I taught my first Turbo Kick class!!! What a fun year of growth for me as an instructor, coach & woman.  I was so scared the first night I showed up to teach, worried I would fail, worried no one would come to my class, or that they would never come back! Last week one of my gym coworkers was telling me how he remembered when I started.. being shy, in & out of the gym just for class - and now I walk in smiling, confidence rolling off my shoulders & take charge! I laughed, but his words are true! I found a piece of myself that I didn't know was missing when I started instructing. I am in my element.  I love it, I am inspired by those who take my classes, I am motivated to push harder & I am so proud of the dedication I see in my frequent rockstars.  I talk about accountability, and a very wise friend I have made through class - says Constistency is key.  She is absolutely right!! You have to be consistent in your actions/choices every day.  With consistency, you demand accountability from yourself & you build habits that are a lifestyle not a fad!! (ps: sorry for the sweaty mug, but this was right after class & let me tell you I certainly earned my shower today!)
#instahealth #wellness #fitness #instructor #coach #followme #myfitlife #annivesary #confidence #findyourawesome #turbomom

849566226632842208_292321957.caption:
From the bottom of my heart I am so grateful for not only Herbalife nutrition products but for the amazing people and family I've made along with it. I would've never been able to do it by just eating clean and I for SURE never would've been able to do it without alone. 
The picture on the left was from my trip to Ontario just over a month ago. Back up to 146 lbs I still loved what I was doing but I lost a lot of love for myself. I was confused with nutrition, body image, self love and taking care of myself in general. I was in a really dark and lonely place; even though I was surrounded by love, I didn't believe it. I didn't want to ruin the impression of the happy, hyper person everyone had of me so I didn't use the supportive community like I should have. 
That weekend I re-learned how to appreciate the little things: mother-daughter time, driving up north alone while listening to Bon Iver (incredibly peaceful, I suggest it to everyone), the beauty in nature, meeting new people and rekindling old, thought to be lost relationships. 
That week after came at perdect timing after the reset of the weekend. I got to become friends, hang out, laugh with and pick the brains of two of the people I had looked up to for a while: @nicolie21 and @sirstyle . I learned soooo much from them and will never forget the week I had with them. I was given a lot of simple advice that really got through to me, but I was also SHOWN a love for life that started to rub off on me. The weekend after was just an amazing continuation of that week! 
I am not ashamed of my struggle, only that I didn't use the support and love that I was and am showered with. Physically, its a 7 lb difference.  Mentally, its a complete 180. I have such a love for life, so much energy and true confidence and I just want to help everyone feel this amazing, its that simple. This company, these people, these nutrition products and this family is just indescribably amazing.

Truth is, there is not a single day that passes by nowadays where I don't give thanks for having the use of a car. Baby ferrying duties aside, having a car gives me the option to take off for an hour or so during lunch, to get some quiet time alone. As much as I want and love being a mom, the hardest thing about motherhood (for me, at least) is the loss of self. Where did that girl go? Overnight I became a mom and everything that I was before is now secondary. Dealing with that is more difficult than one could imagine. These one hour time-outs - so precious - allow me to be just me again.

888745008308253003_4666883.caption:
So today is the last day of my 2 precious weeks of leave. I have not completed anything that I planned to do. I did not finish reading that Bill George book. I did not declutter the cupboards. I baked nothing. Studied nothing. 
Instead, I spent a lot of time sitting at the patio. I saw how the sun fell on the leaves and how the blades on the bushes fluttered in the wind. I dilly-dallied away mornings with the little boy, laughing loudly and often arriving in school way past breakfast time. Twice, he fell asleep in the car and instead of going to school, I drove him to Ya Kun where I ate French toast and read the papers, waiting for him to wake up. 
I drove to places I've never driven to before. Sat in cafes once or twice, with a book but never really reading. I looked at people, saw how they hugged. Watched parents sending kids to school for the first time, with smiles that masked the awkwardness of Day One. Driving home today, I thought about my parents, wondered if they knew about Ryan Boy. Maybe love transcends boundaries that time and death put in place. Maybe in the kiss of the sunshine, in the comfort of shadows and in the caress of the wind when it blows, they love him though me. How much I miss them still.

There was plenty of time for day dreaming. A lot of piano playing. Listening. Somehow the wind chimes ring louder this time of the year. I achieved nothing that I set out to do. Yet I feel like I have achieved everything.

838714764168098299_4666883.caption: 9 am. We just had breakfast, I'm going to cook chicken curry and the aircon man is dropping by to fix the waterfall that is happening in our bedroom. Later, I'm going for a hair cut with a book in tow and the boys have plans to hang out by the pool or on the patio swing. There are no high heels today, just pretty flip flops and pedicured toes. I think Saturday is building up nicely.

850508222524387870_4666883.caption: Day 281. That's your toy drum in the picture, the one that goes 1,2,3 and a,b,c, rat-tat-tat-tat-dah! The drum hangs by the side of your bed next to a plastic ball and a cube made of crinkly cloth. Yesterday when you thought that Papa wasn't looking, you crawled there and tapped on the drum and when it came to life -  a,b,c! 1,2,3! rat-da-ta-da-tah! - you scuttled away for your life, shocked by its response. You have 8 teeth now - EIGHT. Imagine! 4 above, 4 below and you look nothing like a baby now. You understand 'no' (at least when Mummy says it. Papa needs to work on it.) and you know that rummaging in the newspaper basket is No, with a capital N. Last night after I put you to sleep, you let out a sigh so soft it was almost imperceptible, yet so full of contentment. I hope that's how your days are, full of discoveries and new adventures and at the end of it all, a safe haven for sleep and rest. #ryaninmyworld

1007060790678483253_4666883.caption: 14-June-15. Cooked a pot of tau yew bak (braised pork in soy sauce) complete with beancurd and eggs while the boy was napping. Followed a method taught by my Ah Ma to my mother and my aunties where you have to first fry the pork in a heated pot until the fat oozes out. Then coat the pot properly with the fat, add garlic. Add soy sauce, dark and light, then sugar. Let the whole concoction caramelise. And all the while, while cooking, I could hear generations of the women in my family all urging me, don't worry, it will not burn-lah. Do not be afraid! Do not add water! And so I left it and true enough it didn't burn and now tomorrow's dinner is settled.

It’s also about not loving someone else, but oneself, and the whole world, at large. In the sense that the Lion manages to draw enjoyment and fulfilment out of loving without ties, without conditions and without expectations. But then, that is ideal, and #Leo does demand returns. Lion’s urge for power and dominance finds its way in the domain of #love too. Leos like submission, and crave assurance. Never the ones to shirk away from giving generously, they do demand that gratitude be expressed with candour and affections be returned with reverence. ♌️🌍💛 #Leo #LeosLove #LeoSeason ##TagALeo

In Jesus' name I pray, Amen.

❤️ • We had a little year-end #TeamGametize powwow this evening and each of us took turns expressing what we were grateful for.

Me? I ended up in a teary, bumbling mess. Moments before, I was trying to make my thoughts coherent but it failed miserably. I ended up spewing out all my insecurities (I know, what a way to spoil the year-end mood) and how I was so grateful for the team for standing by me despite me being a burden.

But seriously, my insecurities aside - I had enough time on the way home to reorganize my thoughts more coherently; #TeamGametize is like my second family. They've stood by me through all my ups and downs and just being with them cheers me up a great deal. Despite living in a society that judges you for your "usefulness" (and where the weaklings get dissed), I always felt loved and accepted by them and this felt even more apparent especially in the past couple of years when it all went downhill. Apart from my parents, I have never felt so grateful to anyone else in my entire lifetime.

Seriously. I love love love you guys. I've never felt so emotional before at our year-end gatherings. Thank you for making me laugh and smile when I am down, and for always reassuring me that it'll all be okay in the end (whether work-related or health-related). I've grown stronger and more positive because of all of you. 💪🏻

1123780215753688932_111808.caption:
T H O U G H T S • With the limited energy (and "well days", as I call it) I have, I'm extremely picky about how I spend my time. Quiet lunches/dinners with my parents take precedence, and only one day (of maximum 3 hours) a week to catch up with friends if energy permits and I feel well enough. And nope, I don't allow people into my home either because I'm really strict about my rest time now and there's too much medical shit on my walls.

I gravitate towards quiet places now, where I have space to breathe and think. I think my tolerance towards bullshit and drama has pretty much gone down the drain. (Tolerance might come back in future when I - hopefully - have less on my plate then, but for now just. Nope.) And I avoid excessively negative people like the plague.

Much as I try to gather up energy to meet friends, I can't help but feel as if I'm to blame when we don't catch up for too long. My fault really, as I'm completely not letting anyone in (except one) on what's been happening, so they don't really understand the extent on how bad things can be. I love and miss my friends, but currently it's a self-preservation/survival game for me.

Too many thoughts today because I managed to see some people yesterday who I haven't seen since before I fell ill, and I picked up some ... vibes. Hey, all's well and good among us but just thinking too much here and I can't help but wonder if my other friends are also thinking the same way. Or whether there's something I could be doing better.

Either way, when I see anyone, I'm pretty much a pro at putting on my happy face and pretending everything is okay, even when I actually feel very cui or the pain level is at 8/10. Just so I don't become a shitty companion during that very limited time we have together.

超级 long post, sorry.

K E E P  L O O K I N G  UP • With Mondays to Wednesdays dedicated to work, and Thursdays to Fridays for medical appointments/hospital visits, I'm completely spent and energy-depleted by the time Saturday rolls around. And I end up spending the entire weekend resting at home apart from the occasional dinner with parents. 
Someone forgot to mention "nonexistent social life" under the symptoms list for autoimmune illnesses. Sorry friends, that it's been so difficult to ask me out the past year and a half. I am still only at 60-70% and unfortunately still improving slowly. But still positive that things continue getting better.

For those who are saying I look better - trust me, it's the clothes and the concealer. And perhaps only because I've started smiling more again recently - if anything has improved dramatically in the past 6 months, it's my mood.

So yep, I'll just keep looking up.

Throwback to 2 weeks ago at Dad's secret hideout.

Been reflecting on the whole of 2015 and I have to describe it as "one step forward, two steps back". I retired my #getwellby2015 hashtag several months ago when it became evident that this is a lifelong problem (again) so there is no "get well" to speak of but more of learning to live with it.

So learning I am, all over again. I think I'm doing a pretty okay job, but I still wish I could do better. But another lesson learnt is that you can't set deadlines on your body's recovery so I've removed all my expectations.

It's been a bad bad week and I pretty much had to rest at home all over again. But there's still 3 weeks left of 2015 so I'll try to make it count. ✌🏻️

806771506302807760_199071402.caption: FIRST OFF, if you didn't read my comment in the last pic, I changed the instructions for you to repeat the section only 88 times. Sorry! Anyway, this #knitalong will be found under the hash tag #pdxmexKAL! Happy knitting!Next section (this is a short section): Continuing from previous section... Row 1: sl3 WYIF, move yarn back and K4, sl4 WYIF.Row 2: K all sts.Repeat rows 1 and 2 three more time (of this section.Row 9: Repeat row 1 of this section.Row 10 (You will be making a one row buttonhole): K4, WYIF, sl1 and slip back onto left needle. You will now bind off 4 sts without knitting. To do this, (sl1, pass second sts on right needle over first sts off of the needle) 4 times. Sl1 sts from right needle to left. Turn work around to RS. Using the cable cast on method, CO 5 sts (one extra than bound off). Turn work to WS. Sl1 from left to right and pass second stitch over off right needle to reinforce buttonhole. K remaining sts.Repeat rows 1 and 2 of this section three more times.I cord bind off:Cable cast on 4 sts.K3, k2tog. Slip all sts on right needle on to left and repeat until the 4 sts of the I cord remain. K all 4 sts together. Break yarn and sew in all ends to complete this section. (fellow knitters, this was how I learned to make a buttonhole and it always worked for me. If you have your own way, you may do so. Just be sure its worked on this row or close.) #knitting #knittersofinstagram #KAL #yarn #yarnporn

If you have an extra skein of sport weight yarn laying around, and need a hat this winter, join me for an impromptu #knitalong!! I'll be posting pics and pattern instructions along the way! I LIVE HERE! haha #portland #oregon #pdx regram @instagram
In the northernmost part of Portland, Oregon, the iconic St. John’s Bridge extends across the Willamette River. Though the bridge has become known for its green hue and distinctly pointed towers, the park underneath has also come to enjoy a fame of its own.

The bridge's stylized architecture continues even into its soaring concrete supports, which resemble the arches of a Gothic cathedral. Taking its name from the supports, Cathedral Park opened in 1980—a stark change from what had nearly been a junkyard beneath the bridge a decade earlier.

Now, the park's lush meadow spaces, proximity to the river and dramatic backdrops create a special draw for local and visiting Instagrammers, making the space a favorite for creative outings and InstaMeets.

For more photos and videos from Cathedral Park, tap the blue location text above.

807315068413144566_199071402.caption: #pdxmexkalFor this section, I'm using what I call "extended linen stitch". Knitting will get a bit tight and may affect the gauge. Remember, this project is a bit improvised so bear with me!Continuing on:Row 1: K2, sl2 WYIF. Repeat until the end of round. (use a stitch marker if needed.) Repeat row twice more.Row 4: sl2 WYIF, K2. Repeat until the end of round.Repeat row twice more.Repeat these 6 rows (x) times.I'll keep you updated on how many rows I do. Happy knitting! :) #knitting #knittersofinstagram #yarn #knitalong #KAL

MAKING A DIFFERENCE
Day twelve of the @earth_hq #winterwellness photo challenge. This was taken February last year after completing a charity bike ride in Cambodia for @projectfutures . We rode 400km over 10 days but the last two days were 90km and 105km. Needless to say it was tough but boy was it a life changing experience. My hubby and I raised $14,000 to go on the trip and it went towards bringing awareness to sex trafficking in Cambodia. Little girls as young as 3 are sold into the sex trade. As part of the trip we visited an AFESIP centre where we got to meet some of the young girls that have been rescued. Tears were shed but the girls were so full of love giving us hugs and sharing their culture with us. I will never forget this trip and Cambodia will always have such a special place in my heart.
#earthhq #businesschicks

6 FITNESS AND EXERCISE MYTHS YOU SHOULD BE AWARE OF

These days, an abundance of well-meaning, yet dodgy advice on all things nutrition and exercise means we often find ourselves pushing, depriving and punishing ourselves — with little result. 
We practice the so-called healthy habits we’re unknowingly led to believe will help us release those pesky kilos, tone our bods and increase our longevity, when in actuality, they’re completely wasting our time.

Worse still, some of those exercise and healthy-eating plans can do more harm than good.

False hopes and promises, you could say.

Today, we’ve turned to in-the-know Personal Trainer and Health Coach Kylie Anderson @be_your_radiant_self  to help us dissect some of the more common and misleading exercise and fitness myths out there and reveal the real truth behind each one.

981975770576253030_370103899.caption: Happy Mother's Day to all Mothers. You are more than appreciated!!! Essential Keys: Trustworthy, Good, Works Hard, Extra Mile, Wise, Great Example, Prepared, Keeps Herself Cared for, Makes You Look Good, Hopeful, Calm, Loves God!  Who can find a virtuous and capable wife? She is more precious than rubies. Her husband can trust her, and she will greatly enrich his life. She brings him good, not harm, all the days of her life. She finds wool and flax and busily spins it. She is like a merchant’s ship, bringing her food from afar. She gets up before dawn to prepare breakfast for her household and plan the day’s work for her servant girls. She goes to inspect a field and buys it; with her earnings she plants a vineyard. She is energetic and strong, a hard worker. She makes sure her dealings are profitable; her lamp burns late into the night. Her hands are busy spinning thread, her fingers twisting fiber. She extends a helping hand to the poor and opens her arms to the needy. She has no fear of winter for her household, for everyone has warm clothes. She makes her own bedspreads. She dresses in fine linen and purple gowns. Her husband is well known at the city gates, where he sits with the other civic leaders. She makes belted linen garments and sashes to sell to the merchants. She is clothed with strength and dignity, and she laughs without fear of the future. When she speaks, her words are wise, and she gives instructions with kindness. She carefully watches everything in her household and suffers nothing from laziness. Her children stand and bless her. Her husband praises her: “There are many virtuous and capable women in the world, but you surpass them all!” Charm is deceptive, and beauty does not last; but a woman who fears the LORD will be greatly praised. Reward her for all she has done. Let her deeds publicly declare her praise. (‭Proverbs‬ ‭31‬:‭10-31‬ NLT) #MothersDay #Wisdom #Love #Prepared #Precious #Praise #Hopeful #Calm #Virtuous

597438659199606801_11457919.caption:
Crazy story...
We are giving out hot chocolate at the buss station  and praying for people.  The lady on the left side came to get some hot chocolate but unfortunately was shaking because she was cold. So Jenayda felt in her heart to bless her and decides to give her her favorite sweater. The lady was very great-full and left to catch her buss.  Later on Victoria comes and tells us that the same lady was crying because earlier she was praying to God that he might keep her warm. She said God didn't just provide hot coco but also a warm sweater. She said that lately she has been praying and reading her Bible more to get closer to God and that this situation was a reminder that God is taking care of her. Someone else's sacrifice might be someone else's prayer being answered. Be obedient to God when he whispers. It may be small but great things come in small packages. "Jesus birth".
Remember. "Little things are just little things but faithfulness in those little things are a BIG deal." #jesus #story #love #hope

Indonesian Batik is a cloth that is traditionally made using a manual wax-resist dyeing technique.

Originating from Java, batik is made by drawing designs on fabric using dots and lines of hot wax, which resists dyes and therefore allows the artisan to color selectively by soaking the cloth in one color, removing the wax with boiling water and repeating. #batik #batiking #yogyakarta #indonesia #love

992905171043267944_199007988.caption: My obsession with brass comes from my nana and granddad. Their house is full of it from their time spent overseas. A colonel in the Air Force he flew 30 missions in Germany during WWII and spent many years in Iran and Pakistan where he survived an assassination attempt while in the shower because he dropped his bar of soap and was retrieving it while the bullet came through the window. Not all have been so fortunate to cheat death and my heart goes out to them all. I come from a big military family and have the upmost respect for those who serve and the families who experience not only loss but the fear and courage of having their loved ones in harms way.

1152255265538772288_1431820194.caption: St Nicholas, Islip this morning. Beautiful sunshine but now it's pouring with rain and a howling gale out there yet again. #islip #church #northamptonshire

1137786664085818810_1431820194.caption: The nativity scene is installed in All Saints, Great Addington. Their tree is in but not yet decorated. Christmas is on its way that's for sure! #nativity #greataddington #church #northamptonshire

1102793033902132734_1431820194.caption: St John the Baptist, Upton with what Pevsner describes as 'an intensely domestic front". Chancel rebuilt 1842, the rest looks c17 Gothic. The interior looked so interesting but unfortunately it was locked.  Through the windows we could see a monument to William Dove 1633 and his two wives. Perhaps one day I shall find it open. #church #upton #cambridgeshire #countryside

1103058171930545998_1431820194.caption: Old barn at Islip. There was a time when we could wander all round this barn but now it's all fenced off. Health and safety as ever! #barn #islip #ruin #countryside #northamptonshire

1080248179091508657_1431820194.caption: An almost new church for me, St John the Baptist at Keyston. The outside of this one is very familiar but only once before have I found it open. I remember the door making a terrible cracking noise as it opened making me jump out of my skin and such an air of decay and dismalness that I went straight out again. Yesterday I was determined to be braver although I'd forgotten the door so jumped a mile again! The smell and general messiness is apparently caused by bats which I can believe but I made myself explore and although it will never be a favourite I'm glad I had a proper look this time. #stjohnthebaptist #keyston #cambridgeshire #church #chuchinterior

1097037484191321753_1431820194.caption: A little window in Earls Barton church.  It's that stone sill I love so much in this one. #window #church #earlsbarton #northamptonshire

1102732788437814464_1431820194.caption:
Helpston, home of John Clare "the Northamptonshire  Peasant Poet". Clare was a lover of autumn and this is part of his 'To Autumn' poem. "Come, pensive Autumn, with thy clouds and storms
And falling leaves and pastures lost to flowers;
A luscious charm hangs on thy faded forms, 
More sweet than Summer in her loveliest hours.
#johnclare #poet #helpston  #village #northamptonshire #autumn #trees

1089086852822142192_1431820194.caption: All Saints, Sudborough.  In a beautiful village of stone and thatch cottages, this little church is usually open and welcoming. #church #allsaints #sudborough #northamptonshire

1096432749532876150_1431820194.caption: All Saints, Earls Barton with its Saxon tower built in 970 and one of the oldest in Britain. 1087839361149636217_1431820194.caption: St Margaret of Antioch, Knotting. The chancel gates here dated 1637. Set up after cock-fighting had been indulged in in the chancel on Shrove Tuesday in the presence of the rector and the churchwardens. #church #redundantchurch #knotting #bedfordshire

1094992489947008982_1431820194.caption: St James, Dengie, Essex. 14thc with 19thc bellcote. This remote little place was always on my to visit list and had been for years. It took us a while to find the church as it isn't anywhere near the village and we kept seeing signs to the marshes but we never did find those! At least I saw the place at last, I can stop wondering about it now. #church #dengie #essex

1018852120926983481_490255100.caption:
One year ago I somehow managed to convince (maybe trick) my beautiful wife into joining the Emmor Works' crew. She left her awesome job as a business research librarian at UPenn.  It was a bit of a risk given we were putting all of our "financial eggs" in one basket. Thankfully, since her coming on, we have doubled our customer base, seriously improved our customer experience, moved into a bigger space, outgrew the new space and needed to expand again, increased efficiency in both the office and the shop, extended our delivery range, began shipping, developed new products, and did it all while raising our quality standards.

We have a great team of guys (and gals) over here and it is only improving as we all learn together. We're excited to see what the upcoming year will bring but I'm super thankful to have such a great wife as a friend and business partner. Thanks Melinda for joining the team.

1031178581968374786_268463538.caption:
After everything that has come my way this past year I can honestly say I am proud of myself. 
I have learned to control my emotions instead of the other way around, I no longer have slumped shoulders and my nearly permanent rain cloud following me around. I have learned to communicate properly, to be 100% honest with everyone, and to intelligently/tactfully communicate my feelings. 
I have become a better partner, mother, animal care taker, yogi, and cook. I am finally able to practice my religion freely, with no judgments, and I have finally found "Alex" or Tigerlilly, my new name. Since making sure to try to always let positive thoughts fill my mind and quickly rid myself of any and all negativities through clean eating, yoga, meditation, and my  spirituality I have come so far, further than I ever imagined I could come. 
Even though I have been feeling defeated in so many ways lately I WILL NOT let it get to me. Thanks to those of you that have truly stuck with me through the years, which is not many at all, I could not have done it without my never ending support and shoulder to cry on, Brandon. 
I am hoping to meet some amazing friends of my own on this journey. I will continue my path to enlightenment until my dying day, chasing happiness, justice, love, and wisdom. I strive to be the change I wish to see in the world and I hope that I can inspire others around me to do the same. 
#bethechange #rantoftheday #motivation #inspiration #proud #wisdom #inspire

1085041567856775166_1023882226.caption:
Recipe of the Week: Lemon Chia Seed Protein Cookies
Just look at these sweet, bright and sunshiny cookies that are healthy enough for breakfast! They're packed with extra nutrients and protein#healthy#yummy#protein#cookies#recipe

Ingredients: 
1/4 cup coconut flour
2 scoops vanilla protein powder
3/4 tsp baking powder
1/2 tsp xanthan gum
1 tbs chia seeds
1 tbs lemon zest
1 1/2 tbs coconut oil melted
1 large egg
3 tbs freshly squeezed lemon juice
1/4 cup dates puréed 
Directions: 
1. If you don't have a food processor. Boil 5-6 dates so they soften. Blend the dates with a bit of water so the dates don't stick.
2. In a small bowl whisk the coconut flour, protein powder, baking powder and lemon zest. In a separate bowl mix egg and coconut oil. Stir in lemon juice and date purée. 
3. Stir in the coconut flour mixture until completely incorporated. Rest for 10 minutes.
4. While cookie dough rests. Preheat oven 180 degrees Celsius and line a baking sheet with baking paper. 
5. Drop the cookie dough into 12 rounded scoops and flatten to desired thickness and width. Bake for 11-13 minutes. Cool the cookies on the baking sheet for 10 minutes before turning out on a wire rack.

1 bunch asparagus 
1 medium eggplant 
3 corn ears 
2 medium zucchini 
1 red pepper/capsicum 
1/4 infused herb oil 
300-500g cherry tomatoes 
1/4 cup fresh basil leaves 
100g feta 
Dressing:
1/4 herb infused oil 
Zest half of lemon 
1/4 juice from a lemon 
1 tsp Dijon mustard
Black pepper
1/2 tsp salt

Ingredients:
1. Hear grill.
2. Cut eggplant into thick slices. Shave skin off and salt both sides. Let it sit.
3. Husk the corn and place on a tray.
4. Cut ends of zucchini and cut in half 
5. Cut hard ends off asparagus and place with other vegetables.
6. Cut red capsicum in half. Remove core and seeds. Place halves on tray.
7. Rinse and dry eggplant and place in tray.
8. Brush all vegetables with your choice of infused oils.
9. Lay out on your grill. As each side chars turn to other side. Depending on your grill friends on cooking time. 
10. Chop vegetables to bite size and place in a large bowl. Cut tomatoes in half and add yo bowl. 
11. Mix all dressing ingredients and basil into bowl and toss to combine. 
12. Top with crumbled feta.

#cookies#oats#ricotta#cinnamon#bananas#recipe#easy#yum#healthy#snack#family#enjoy

Ingredients:
I cup oats
1 desert spoon nut butter (optional)
1/2 cup light ricotta
2 small bananas
I desert spoon of maple syrup or honey or a handful of steamed blended dates
I handful of sultanas
1 egg white 
1/4 tsp Cinnamon and 
1/2 tsp baking powder

Directions:
Preheat oven 200 degrees Celsius. Put bananas in a medium bowl and mash. 
If using dates: steam then before blending. 
Blend steamed dates with water if using dates. 
Place all ingredients in the bowl and mix well. Dollop onto a baking tray and bake for 15 mins. Done! Enjoy 😀

1049726271742987998_1023882226.caption:
Recipe of the Week: Chicken Enchilada Casserole 
Here is another delicious Mexican dish. This enchilada casserole is also known as Stacked Chicken Enchilada. Full of yummy flavours and so easy to make. It's a great healthy dish for the family or when you have visitors to enjoy😀
#recipe#mexican#enchilada#yummy#healthy#family#friends#enjoy

Ingredients: 
3 cups enchilada sauce (see below)
16 corn tortillas halved
2 cans black beans rinsed and drained
1 can while kernel corn drained
3 green onions thinly sliced
4 cups chopped cooked chicken 
3 cups grated cheddar cheese
1 avocado diced
1/2 cup chopped cilantro

Directions:
1. Heat oven 180 degrees Celsius. PrePare large baking dish with cooking spray.
Pour about 3/4 cup enchilada sauce in dish and spread until bottom is coated. Top with a layer of about 8 tortilla halves. Sprinkle evenly with 1 cup of black beans, 1/2 cup corn and green onions. 
2. Then sprinkle heap of chicken and 3/4 cup cheese. 
3. Repeat second layer of tortillas, sauce, beans, corn, chicken and cheese. 
4. Then final layer of tortillas, sauce etc. cover with aluminium foil and bake 20minutes.
(Reserve 3/4 cup of cheese)
5. Remove pan and foil. Sprinkle the top with remaining cheese and return to oven. Bake for another 5-10 minutes or until cheese is melted. 
6. Remove pan and sprinkle avocado and cilantro. 
Serve warm. Enjoy😀

Red Enchilada Sauce:
2 tbs rice bran oil
2 tbs all purpose or gluten free flour 
4 tbs chilli powder
1/2 tsp garlic powder
1/2 tsp cumin
1/4 tsp oregano
2 cups chicken or vegetable stock reduced salt

Directions: 
Heat oil in a small saucepan over medium heat. Add flour and stir for 1 minute. 
Stir in the remaining seasonings and gradually add in the stock. Whisking constantly to remove lumps. Reduce heat and simmer 10 mins or until thick.

Ingredients:

Week 3: Workout 1 of Pre Festive Fitness Challenge 🏃🏼💪🏻🎄
Core 200
This workout will challenge your core strength. Each round has 200 reps of core exercises including your deeper core muscles such as the pelvic floor and transverse abdominis (TA). It's important to build strength on these muscles after having a baby. 
Many people think Ab crunches are the way forward. But they can cause more damage than good. There are many other core exercises that are more beneficial and safer. (Do not do crunches if you are pregnant or recently postnatal. I'll explain further in another post). Please don't do this challenge if your baby is younger than 4 months as you need to gradually build up your core strength. 
Feel strong, be determined, keep motivated! You can do this!💪🏻

1041668060217527666_1023882226.caption:
Recipe of the Week: Fuel to Go Muffins
This nutrient dense muffin tastes amazing and fills you up. This is a great muffin for breakfast or as a snack. 
#recipe#healthy#yummy#fuel#muffins#snack#breakfast#nutritious#eatwell#healthylifestyle

Ingredients:
2 cups of multi grain or wholemeal flour
1 tbs cinnamon
2 tsp baking powder
1/2 cup shredded coconut
1/2 cup dried cranberries or dried blueberries 
2 cups grated carrots
1 shredded Apple
Small can of crushed pineapple 
1/2 cup sunflower seeds
1/2 cup pumpkin seeds
1/4 cup chia seeds
3 eggs
2/3 olive oil/coconut oil/ricebran oil 
1 tsp vanilla 
Instructions: 
1. Mix together flour, cinnamon and baking powder in a large bowl. 
2. Add dried fruit, coconut, seeds, pineapple, carrot and apple. Stir Ro combine.
3. In a separate bowl whisk eggs with oil and vanilla. 
4. Combine this mixture with dry ingredients and blend well. This will be very thick. 
5. Fill 12 cupcake baking cups heaping full. 
6. Bake 180 degrees Celsius and bake for 30 minutes depending on your oven it could be 5 mins more or less.

966994326863845580_308220613.caption: I thought it might be nice to put a face & name to the journal entries I've been sharing--this precious man in the middle is my granddaddy [with me on the left and my sister on the right]. His name is Harris Edgar Moncrief but was more affectionately known as "Sonny." His life wasn't especially spectacular; he wasn't famous or rich; he didn't change the world. But he was a great man; he was kind and jolly; he was artistic and a freethinker; and he cared about people. He was special to those that knew & loved him and in that way he did live spectacularly. I was very young when he left this world, just shy of 7 years old, but I have always missed him. And now reading his journals has helped me finally understand all that I was missing out on. I would have loved more time with him. But since I can't have that, I guess getting to know him through his journals is a pretty good consolation prize. Getting to share him with all of you is just an added bonus. Thanks for sharing in the journey with me. XOXO

967689620471520106_308220613.caption: This journal entry of my granddaddy's is less historical in nature and more personal. Before you read it, it might help you to have a little background on his life at the time he wrote it: He and my Grandmawmaw loved each other but just couldn't work it out so they were divorced (for about a year and a half at this point); he rarely got to see his kids; he worked in a textile mill making very little money (not his dream job for sure); and he suffered with asthma. This is why he started journaling in the first place--trying to cope with the "loss" of his family and with his loneliness. My hope is that this serves to give someone else hope if you're feeling down or going through a rough patch. March 14, 1961: "I was blue last nite and this morning, but I'm feeling better now, thanks to the consolation of God. Seems like I always get down in the dumps when I'm off from work a day and especially after I have had the kids for a weekend. I feel the presence of God and He, and He alone, gives me courage to go on when my strength has gone. I have been wandering in the 'backside of the desert' for a long time. In the process I have found that the only 'set of real values' are those that are God-given or God-inspired. Otherwise man is just a vagabond. I skipped through the Bible tonite and read a passage here and there. The words are still wonderful and strengthening. Of course I do[n't] understand or comprehend it all, but it is like what the Apostle Paul wrote--'We see darkly through a glass,' but one day we shall see clearly." Even in his darkest times, he found hope. Find what gives you hope and cling to it.

A Stormy Sunrise in Queensland, Austral
iaWhen we arrived the clouds were thick and covering the horizon. I wasn't sure there would be a sunrise at all. But man was I wrong.
As the sun started to show it lit up these dramatic clouds which made for one of those epic sunrises that are so common in Queensland.
There really is nothing like being on the coast at sunrise. The peacefulness and just the crashing of the waves seem to make all your cares go away.  #exploringtheglobe #all_shots #magic_photography #globaldaily #insta_international #wonderful_places #thisisqueensland #australia #worldplaces

846936039176351558_6591354.caption:
Sunset over Oia in Santorini, Greece.
When you think of stunning sunsets it is hard not to think of Santorini. 
It seems that everywhere you go on the island you can take in a beautiful view.
Oia is the most popular place for sunset and you can see why. The beautiful white buildings combined with the colours of sunset make a perfect scene.  #exploringtheglobe #all_shots #greece #magic_photography #globaldaily #insta_international #santorini #wonderful_places

1120227146595642570_6591354.caption:
Clouds roll in over the stoic rock formations of Meteora, Greece.

Even when the weather is bad the landscape is beautiful. The first few days of our visit here were rainy and cloudy and I loved it. 
It seemed so mysterious. This is definitely a place that I could come back to again and again. 
#visitmeteora #greece #ig_greece

1078463079493480141_6591354.caption:
Natures mirror on the Lemaire Channel in Antarctica.

Antarctica is one magical place. I thought that maybe I would get sick of ice but with formations like this I could gaze at them all day.
We were quite lucky at this time of year as we were able to get far down into this channel. Let me just say it was worth it.

Antarctica is another one of those places that should be at the top of your bucket list.
#ice #antarctica #reflection

1102108506050604386_6591354.caption:
Looking over the Rousanou Monastery in the Meteora Valley.

I am simply awe struck at the beautiful formations here in Meteora, Greece.
As we drive around it seems like there are magnificent views around every corner.
The weather was not the best today but the dramatic clouds and swirling mists made for a feeling like you are on another planet.
I can't wait to explore more of this unique landscape.
#visitmeteora #visitgreece #greece

1006399336119175832_1454621185.caption: Good morning, friends!  I'm up early.  Couldn't stop coughing, so I figured I might as well start my day!  I'm sure to be passed out again by 10:30am though. 😂 I was going over a couple of the tags I managed to catch while sick, and wanted to share them today.  My lovely friend Dawn @dg825 asked me to share #10thingsthatmakemehappy, and my equally lovely friend Chelsea @chelsea_stylemutthome asked me to share #widn.  Well I think I covered #widn so I'll move on to #10things 1. My faith-It's my foundation, and without it I'd be flying around like a person in outer space.  2. My little family-Each day they teach me what it means to be a good person.  I look forward to any and all time we have to spend together. 3. Traveling-It's food for my soul!  To see how other people live on a daily basis is interesting to me, and to have the time to relax and regroup is necessary. 4. Home Decor/Decorating- I love to shop for interesting pieces, and bring them home and make them work. I can't wait for the day when I can do the same for someone else!  5. All things coastal-Seriously, I might have a problem with this one.  I'm doing my best to refrain from painting my walls blue and sanding my floors and staining them a weathered gray.  I want to live in a beach house, but I'm reserving that for the day I can actually afford a real one!  Don't hold me accountable to that though.  It all just might happen one day!  6. Movies-Movies have been our preferred date since we were in HS.  On the rare chance we actually get to do something alone, you'll probably catch us at the movies.  7. Food-I'm a foodie!  I like to eat out, sometimes I try new things, but I always have a favorite dish everywhere I go.  8. Weight Loss-Haha!  I lost all the baby weight over a year ago, after having my son, however the not so fun stress monster has caused me to eat my emotions and gain quite a bit back.  I'm looking forward to reigning it all in and getting back to "me". 9. Blogging-It's a nice stress reliever to have a goal and complete it for a blog post.  I tend to stress when I have nothing major going on. 10. Photography-I enjoy snapping pictures of just about everything!  Continued below....

If You Can Count Your Money, Get Back To Work.

Written by: @fitbusinessman

We do not celebrate before crossing our defined finish line.

The list of "almost made it there" individuals is a long one.

It's way too easy to get distracted on your climb to success and stop to enjoy the fruits you have gathered.

But, have you reached your goal?

If not, don't stop to smell the money.

It's just money.

It's just one resource you can direct toward your goal, but it is not the goal itself.

Regain the laser-like focus and keep visualizing the goal. See your vision daily. Make it real...daily.

The second you stop to count your winnings, you have given your competition the advantage.

@fitbusinessman
@fitbusinessman

1065059261997491044_1143226639.caption:
Old Road, Lamayuru.
Located high above the swanky new NH1, the old highway now seems to have been forgotten. The road takes you through the stunning Snow Leopard Conservancy Area and quaint little villages often unheard of. In the time I was behind the wheel, there was rain through one pass, sleet through another and snow on the last one.

I had been to Leh twice before but never saw it for more than just another overcrowded tourist town. This year, four visits in just as many months with each lasting for at least a week, I got to see a side of Leh which few experience. From walking down the hidden alleys of the city to driving through roads which few know exists, the journey has only begun.

Royal Enfield continues to be one of the few selected dependable motorcycles who can claim bragging rights in the terrain. How this air filter managed to effortlessly survive in spite of being covered in small rocks and stones is beyond my understanding.

1020122802379399784_1143226639.caption: On a freezing, late-winter morning, I dared to stop in the middle of an army cantonment on the Kargil-Leh road to ask the personnel if the remote CCD outlet was open to public. 1052114189045939950_1469378790.caption:
Shahd Mahdi is a 13 yr old girl from #Iraq. In March of 2008 when Shahd was only six yrs old a rocket fell on her #home which resulted in her losing her left leg. Unable to treat her locally in Iraq the #family reached out to the PCRF for #help. We arranged for her to #travel for care a total of three times so far, once in 2008, a second time in 2011, and again in June of this year.

In previous trips she had surgery to revise her stump and was fitted with a #prosthetic leg. After outgrowing her old prosthesis and not being able to use it anymore, she is now undergoing care to get fitted for a new prosthetic #leg that will fit her better and help her to walk again. Shahd and her mom are under the care of our PCRF #Cleveland Chapter and volunteers from the #Canton community. Special thanks to Kevin Montini and his office Yanke Bionics for always committing themselves to help us help our PCRF #kids.

887857911184251382_191997581.caption:
Watching the sun set on the last day of the year. It's been the craziest one yet. It started with 8 months of chef school and ended with a job I love and the start of my culinary career. I got sick a lot, I relapsed a few times, I fell down, I wanted to give up.
But I also fought back, bettered myself and my future. I gave myself another chance, I worked hard, I learned the hard way and I kept going. I did my first cons and made some sweet bank on the beads. I made new friends, lost a few that didn't want the best for me, I gave up a few who's bitterness I don't need in my life. But most of all. I loved. I gave my all to everyone as I always do and I got to spend more time with my family than I have in the last week years. Next year is a mystery but I'm ready to open the door. 
Happy New Years my friends. 🎉🎊🍸 Be strong and be proud of how far you've come, no matter how far that is.. #happynewyear #sunset #borderlinepersonalitydisorder

1076037882715426374_1066906.caption:
Last night I tried Dave Ahern's aka corkgourmetguy's first permanent venture, @Wahleeahsw6... Home to an extensive craft beer list, every dish paired to a great beer, and every dish cooked with a great beer!  Now being a Filipino at heart, I had to have the potted pigs cheeks for my starter... Seriously tasty! The only problem with it? Once I had this followed by the insanely good Wahleeah burger, I had no room for dessert (this has been a problem lately!) so needless to say, I have to go back for pudding... And to try some different starters too! If you are around Fulham sometime soon, make sure you check these guys out! I give a massive thumbs up to anyone who makes everything themselves from scratch in the food world!
